status_message:
Smugglers had promised 33-year-old Sabeel that $400 would buy him passage to Europe on a cargo ship or a fishing trawler. The reality: A 20-foot-long inflatable dinghy, powered by an outboard motor.

Built for 25 people, 133 were squeezed in. An hour after one of the smugglers took the migrants out to sea, he left the vessel ‚Äî taking a fast boat back to land.

"See those stars," he told the migrants, pointing upward before he left. "They mean north. Follow them."

Suddenly ocean and sky were the same color: Black.

This is the story of one desperate day at sea ‚Äì and the rescue mission that saved Sabeel and thousands of others: http://cnn.it/2bEyvcO
link_name: "These crossings are nothing but fatal"

status_message: BREAKING NEWS: President Barack Obama will win Florida, CNN projects. http://on.cnn.com/S8VAR5 It was the only state that had remained uncalled in the presidential race. With the state‚Äôs 29 electoral votes, the final nationwide tally is 332 electoral votes for Obama, 206 for Mitt Romney. Obama reached the needed 270 electoral votes for victory shortly after 11 p.m. Tuesday, based on CNN projections. Romney called the president to concede about an hour later. In 2008, by comparison, when Obama also won Florida, he had a total of 365 electoral votes to John McCain‚Äôs 173 electoral votes. Long lines at polling places, lengthy ballots and a large number of absentee ballots delayed the final count in Florida.
link_name: Obama wins Florida, CNN projects
